Moonraker / Klipper 3D Printer Driver for Hubitat
Author: jdthomas24  |  Version: 1.0.0
Monitor and control your Klipper 3D printer from Hubitat. Works with Sonicpad and standard installs (Raspberry Pi, BTT Pi, CB1, etc.).
---
What You Get
aaStatusTile — live dashboard showing printer name, online/klipper state, current print, hotend & bed temps vs target, progress bar, elapsed/remaining time, ETA, fan speed, and filament status.
filesListTile — recent prints browser showing your top 20 most recently printed files. Currently printing file pinned green at #1. Last completed print highlighted at top. Use the file number with `startPrint` to reprint any file.
Both tiles are added to your Hubitat dashboard as Attribute tiles.
---
Installation
Drivers Code → New Driver — paste the driver code and Save
Devices → Add Device → Virtual — name it to match your printer (e.g. `3D - CR10 Pro 1`)
Set Type to `Moonraker Klipper Printer` → Save Device
Enter your preferences → Save Preferences
Repeat for each printer.
---
Setup
Sonicpad
All printers share one IP — one Hubitat device per printer, each with a different port:
Sonicpad USB Port	Moonraker Port
Port 1	7125
Port 2	7126
Port 3	7127
Port 4	7128
Standard Install
Each printer has its own IP. Use the port configured in your `moonraker.conf` (commonly `7125`).
Key Preferences
Printer IP / Port — see above
Temperature Unit — Celsius (default) or Fahrenheit
Poll Interval — 10–30 seconds recommended while printing
Recent Files Limit — top 20 recommended
API Key — only needed if your Moonraker enforces authentication
---
Attributes for Automations & Rules
`printState` · `filename` · `lastPrint` · `error` · `currentLayer` · `totalLayers` · `chamberTemp (°C)` · `mcuTemp (°C)`
---
Troubleshooting
Issue	Fix
"klipper: unknown" in tile	Hit Initialize — fixes on next poll
Wrong temperature unit	Preferences → switch to Celsius → Save Preferences
"0 prints done" in tile	Hit Refresh File List
Printer shows offline but is on	Hit Refresh or Initialize
startPrint fails	Verify IP/port in preferences and that Moonraker is running
`filePathCache` in State Variables	Normal — used internally by `startPrint` to resolve file numbers to full paths
